 land developer to a developer of prime commercial properties in july  bce inc sold  ownership in bce development to carena developments ltd controlled by the toronto branch of the bronfman family bced was renamed brookfield development inc now brookfield asset management followed in  by the remaining  montreal trustedit in march  bce bought a  stake in montreal trust from power financial for million the diversification was considered a natural evolution due to bces longstanding interest in financial services its familiarity in selling services to the public and its inhouse money management operations in  bce sold montreal trust to scotiabank for about million taking a substantial loss nortel networksedit when bce was created in  northern telecom was transferred from a subsidiary of crtcregulated bell canada to a nonregulated subsidiary of bce in  with nortels acquisition of bay networks the companys name was changed to nortel networks as a consequence of the stock transaction used to purchase bay networks bces holding was diluted to a minority stake in  bce spun out nortel distributing its stock in nortel to its shareholders nortels share price collapsed with the dotcom crash of  and combined with a mishandling of a subsequent accounting investigation the company never fully recovered it was liquidated in  teleglobe incedit in  bce purchased a  stake in memotec data corporation for  million when memotec purchased international telecommunications carrier teleglobe canada from the canadian government in  the company was renamed teleglobe inc in march  bce announced the purchase of the teleglobe shares it did not own for  billion in april  bce announced it was cutting off longterm funding of teleglobe would give up on the company and take a charge of up to  billion in  teleglobe was sold to the tata group and is now known as vsnl international canada in september  it sold its voice and data business for  million telesat canadaedit in  bell canada acquired a minority i