nd expansion  refocus on core business  proposed takeover  expanding again into mass media  major subsidiaries  bell canada  bell media  other holdings  montreal canadiens  maple leaf sports and entertainment  past holdings  bell aliant  bce development  montreal trust  nortel networks  teleglobe inc  telesat canada  transcanada pipelines  corporate governance  references  external links historyedit the bell telephone company of canada ltd was created by an act of parliament on  april  later known as bell canada its charter granted it the right to construct telephone lines alongside all public rightsofway in canada under a licensing agreement with the usbased america bell telephone company bell also manufactured telephones and telephone equipment an activity that would be spun off in a separate company that later became northern telecom and then nortel networks in  all the bell canada group of companies also known as the bell group were placed under a new holding company bell canada enterprises inc bce this corporate reorganization resulted in bell canada and its subsidiaries including northern telecom later nortel networks and over  others becoming subsidiaries of the new holding company bce under the new parent each company was owned directly by bce which had the benefit of freeing the manufacturing company nortel and other holdings from the heavily regulated telephone company bell canada under a variety of leaders bce has embarked on a series of diversifications consolidations and corporate strategies in  bell canada enterprises was renamed bce inc diversification and expansionedit in  a jean de grandpré chairman of bell canada was appointed as the first chairman and chief executive officer of bce bce soon embarked on a major diversification into property development the energy sector financial services and other sectors within a few years it became the first canadian company to report cad billion in profits when jean monty assumed the job of ceo in  he pursued a convergence strategy attempting to combine both content creation and distribution within bce and to take greater advantage of the emerging internet market bces acquisition in  and subsequent financing of overseas carrier teleglobe cost billions of dollars bce sold teleglobe two years later jean monty resigned and was succeeded by michael sabia as ceo refocus on core businessedit michael sabia refocused bce on its core telecommunications business prompting bce to buy back the  share in bell canada that it had sold in  to ameritech which was subsequently acquired by sbc corporation bce also spun off operating units that it did not consider to be core to its business including emergis in  and bell globemedia and telesat canada in  on february   stating the need to remain competitive bell canada announced job cuts of  to  employees by the end of  on april  bce announced that ceo michael sabia was taking a  pay increase his salary being raised from c million a year to  million a year the pay included a  million salary a  million bonus that sabia converted to deferred share units a longterm incentive payout of  million and other compensation the filing shows bell canada also posted record revenue increases for the previous fiscal year under pressure from investors on october   bce announced it would be wound down with its remaining assets converted to an income trust so its income could be distributed directly to shareholders through dividends avoiding corporate taxes the new entity was planned to be named bell canada income fund as part of this restructuring bell aliant offered to take bell nordiq private while remaining separate from the new bell trust due to announced changes in taxation law by the canadian federal government on december   bce announced it would not proceed with its planned conversion to an income trust it then started planning a restructuring that would have eliminated the bce holding company but this was put on hold when the company began attracting takeover bids proposed takeoveredit due to its stagnant share price starting in april  bce was courted for acquisition by pension funds and private equity groups including a consortium led by the canada pension plan investment board with kohlberg kravis roberts as one of the participants a consortium led by the ontario teachers pension plan otpp and a consortium that included cerberus capital management on june   bce accepted a bid of  per share in cash for a total valuation of  billion from the group led by the otpp and including providence equity partners madison dearborn partners merrill lynch global private equity and torontodominion bank the proposed deal would have been the largest acquisition in canadian history and the largest leveraged buyout ever the deal was approved by bce shareholders quebec superior court whose ruling was overturned by the quebec court of appeal but was later upheld by the supreme court of canada and the crtc subject to certain conditions for its corporate governance structure to ensure that bell remained under canadian control see bce inc v  debentureholders for further information due to the tightening of the credit market caused by the subprime mortgage crisis the investment banks financing the deal – led by citigroup deutsche bank and the royal bank of scotland – started negotiations on may   to revise the terms of their loans with higher interest rates and greater restrictions to protect themselves on july   bce announced that a final agreement had been reached on the terms of the purchase with all financing in place and michael sabia left bce with george cope assuming the position of ceo on july  on november   bce announced that kpmg had informed bce that it would not be able to issue a statement on the solvency of the company after its privatization one of the required conditions of the buyout as a result the purchase was cancelled expanding again into mass mediaedit with shaw communications purchasing the global television network vidéotron launching its wireless telephone network with video content as a key selling point and the enormous popularity of wireless and internet video and other media streams at the  vancouver olympics bell once again sought to bring a content provider into its portfolio in september  bell announced a deal to reacquire full control of the broadcasting properties owned by ctvglobemedia including the ctv television network bell also obtained a  interest in the globe and mail ctvglobemedias other major asset with the remaining  owned by the thomson family through this acquisition bell responded to an increasing trend away from traditional cable and satellite delivery channels and towards new distribution methods over the internet and wireless networks the crtc approved the transaction in march  in  bce announced that it had entered an agreement to acquire manitoba telecom services mts in a transaction worth  billion the deal has been approved by both companies shareholders and boards of directors and is expected to close in late  or early  pending regulatory approval from the competition bureau and other agencies major subsidiariesedit as of  bce inc has three main subsidiaries bell canada bell mobility and bell media comprising over  of bces revenue bell canadaedit main article bell canada this is formed primarily of the historic core of the company in central atlantic and northern canada bell aliant distribution ontario quebec atlantic – bell canada cablevision du nord de quebec inc northwestel – northwestel inc télébec northerntel dryden municipal telephone service bell tv – bell expressvu limited partnership bell mediaedit main article bell media bell media is the bce broadcast and media subsidiary in  bce bought the ctv television network for  billion the company combined ctv with its holdings in the globe and mail newspaper to form bell globemedia with bce owning  and thomson newspapers and woodbridge co ltd the remainder in  bce sold its controlling interest in bell globemedia for  million to woodbridge torstar and the ontario teachers pension plan with bce retaining a  stake the company was subsequently renamed ctvglobemedia in  bce bought out the other owners acquiring ctvs specialty television digital media conventional tv and radio broadcasting platforms in august  bce sold its remaining  stake in the globe and mail to woodbridge bell medias subsidiaries bell media tv bell media tv – sports specialty services bell media tv – specialty services other than sports bell media radio bell media astral – radio tv  specialty services other holdingsedit below is partial list of the holdings of the bce conglomerate montreal canadiensedit in  bce partnered with the molson family in acquiring the montreal canadiens hockey club and the bell centre the  million purchase was termed the richest deal in nhl history bces share was reported to be  million maple leaf sports and entertainmentedit in  together with rogers communications and kilmer sports holding company of larry tanenbaum bce acquired maple leaf sports  entertainment owner of the toronto maple leafs professional hockey team bces interest is held in partnership with rogers communications through the holding company  canada inc  owned by rogers and  by bce holding company  canada inc which is in turn  owned by bce and  by bce master trust fund investment fund of bells pension plan kilmer sports and bce also coown the toronto argonauts a team the companies purchased in  bce and kilmer each own  of the team past holdingsedit bell aliantedit bell aliant was a subsidiary company formed in  from the merger of the four bcecontrolled telephone companies serving canadas atlantic provinces in  the operations of bell aliant were consolidated into those of bell canada bce developmentedit bce development was founded as daon development by vancouverbased developer jack poole in  in the mids daon became known for expanding aggressively in the united states the company first entered the american market in  and nearly quadrupled its total assets to  billion in four years it borrowed heavily to finance deals for premium office space and condominium conversions by  the company had assets worth more than  billion when interest rates soared however daon was caught overextended could not meet its debt payments and was forced into a major restructuring with its bankers in  bce acquired  of daon from its creditors and changed its name to bce development corporation in february  in march  it agreed to acquire us  billion of commercial real estate from the american subsidiary of the oxford development group ltd more than doubling bceds portfolio bce stated its goal was to convert from a land developer to a developer of prime commercial properties in july  bce inc sold  ownership in bce development to carena developments ltd controlled by the toronto branch of the bronfman family bced was renamed brookfield development inc now brookfield asset management followed in  by the remaining  montreal trustedit in march  bce bought a  stake in montreal trust from power financial for million the diversification was considered a natural evolution due to bces longstanding interest in financial services its familiarity in selling services to the public and its inhouse money management operations in  bce sold montreal trust to scotiabank for about million taking a substantial loss nortel networksedit when bce was created in  northern telecom was transferred from a subsidiary of crtcregulated bell canada to a nonregulated subsidiary of bce in  with nortels acquisition of bay networks the companys name was changed to nortel networks as a consequence of the stock transaction used to purchase bay networks bces holding was diluted to a minority stake in  bce spun out nortel distributing its stock in nortel to its shareholders nortels share price collapsed with the dotcom crash of  and combined with a mishandling of a subsequent accounting investigation the company never fully recovered it was liquidated in  teleglobe incedit in  bce purchased a  stake in memotec data corporation for  million when memotec purchased international telecommunications carrier teleglobe canada from the canadian government in  the company was renamed teleglobe inc in march  bce announced the purchase of the teleglobe shares it did not own for  billion in april  bce announced it was cutting off longterm funding of teleglobe would give up on the company and take a charge of up to  billion in  teleglobe was sold to the tata group and is now known as vsnl international canada in september  it sold its voice and data business for  million telesat canadaedit in  bell canada acquired a minority interest in satellite telecommunications carrier telesat canada in  bce raised its stake to  at a cost of cad million for the  of shares it did not already own in december  bce announced the sale of telesat to loral space  communications and the public sector pension investment board for cad billion transcanada pipelinesedit in  bce acquired a controlling  stake in transcanada pipelines limited tcpl in  it announced its departure from the energy sector and sold its stake in tcpl for  billion corporate governanceedit as of  the current members of the board of directors of bce are thomas oneill chair barry allen andré bérard ronald brenneman sophie brochu robert brown george cope anthony fell edward lumley robert simmonds carole taylor and paul weiss since inception bce has had four ceos a jean de grandpré  jean monty  michael sabia  george a cope –present referencesedit  a b george cope appointed to the boards of directors and as ceo of bce inc and bell canada press release bce  archived from the original on  july  retrieved    bell canada annual report     httpwwwtheglobeandmailcomreportonbusinessbellrogersnowofficialownersofmlsearticlethe canadian press  bell to keep canadiens stake cbcca retrieved    fp  retrieved   investor   canada’s biggest  companies by market cap cana